This paper is about deep neural networks and their training schemes, which are commonly studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the issue of adversarial examples, which are perturbations that can cause misclassification in deep neural networks, and this topic is often studied in the sub-categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) and cryptography and security (cs.CR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.CV, and cs.AI, followed by cs.NE and cs.CR.
